Iavan Pijoos, News24SA police. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Vuwani &ndash; Limpopo police have launched a manhunt for a group of people who killed a man in Mvelaphanda on Sunday. Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said on Monday the mob chased a man they accused of being a criminal and beat him to death.&nbsp; &ldquo;The deceased was found lying dead in a pool of blood surrounded with an assortment of used items such as stones and wooden poles.&rdquo;No arrests were made. In a separate incident in Hlanganani outside Giyani, a second man was also killed with a sjambok during a mob attack on Sunday.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.